- timestamp: "[2026-01-23 10:16 AM]"
  from: api-architect
  to: frontend-developer
  task_id: "API-001"
  status: "COMPLETED"
  blocking_task: "FE-001"
  message: |
    📢 DEPENDENCY RESOLVED: API-001 is complete, you can now proceed with FE-001
    
    🎯 TASK GUIDANCE: Create authentication BLoC using domain layer contracts
    
    The domain layer contracts are ready for presentation layer integration:
    
    📋 WHAT YOU CAN BUILD:
    1. AuthBloc/AuthCubit (lib/presentation/auth/bloc/)
       - Use SignInWithGoogle use case
       - Handle Either<Failure, User> results in state
       - Display failure messages in UI
    
    2. Auth Screens (lib/presentation/auth/screens/)
       - Login screen with Google Sign-In button
       - Handle loading, success, and error states
       - Navigate on successful authentication
    
    3. Error Handling Widgets
       - Display Failure messages to users
       - Map Failure types to user-friendly messages
       - Show retry options for NetworkFailure
    
    📚 REFERENCE DOCUMENTATION:
    - Domain layer: docs/architecture/domain-layer.md
    - Error handling: docs/architecture/error-handling.md
    
    🔑 KEY REQUIREMENTS:
    - Never access data layer directly from UI
    - Use use cases, not repositories, in BLoC
    - Handle all Failure types in UI
    - Use fold() to handle Either results
    - Keep UI widgets pure (no business logic)
    
    💡 EXAMPLE ERROR HANDLING IN BLOC:
    ```dart
    final result = await _signInUseCase(NoParams());
    result.fold(
      (failure) => emit(AuthError(failure.message)),
      (user) => emit(AuthSuccess(user)),
    );
    ```
    
    ✅ DOMAIN CONTRACTS AVAILABLE:
    - SignInWithGoogle use case: lib/domain/usecases/auth/sign_in_with_google.dart
    - User entity: lib/domain/entities/user.dart
    - Failure types: lib/domain/failures/failure.dart
    
    Ready to start FE-001!
    
    Role: API Architect
- timestamp: "[2026-01-23 10:42 AM]"
  from: backend-engineer
  to: frontend-developer
  task_id: "FE-AUTH-001"
  priority: "HIGH"
  message: |
    🚀 DATA LAYER READY: Authentication repository is available for integration
    
    📦 WHAT'S AVAILABLE:
    - AuthRepository interface implementation
    - Google Sign-In integration
    - Complete exception-to-failure mapping
    - Dependency injection configured
    
    📋 WHAT YOU NEED TO DO:
    1. Create authentication BLoCs using AuthRepository
    2. Build login/logout UI flows
    3. Implement session management
    4. Create user profile screens
    
    📚 INTEGRATION GUIDE:
    See walkthrough.md for complete integration instructions and usage examples.
    
    🔑 KEY API:
    - signInWithGoogle() -> Either<Failure, User>
    - signOut() -> Either<Failure, void>
    - getCurrentUser() -> Either<Failure, User>
    - refreshToken() -> Either<Failure, AuthToken>
    - isAuthenticated() -> Future<bool>
    
    All methods return Either<Failure, T> for explicit error handling.
    
    Role: Backend Engineer
